race.description: Shed Boss Central West Maiden Plate
race.comment: Tricky. SASSY ABBEY (10) resumes for the Baker yard and this is winnable if the well-bred filly is presented forward. Her Rosehill trials suggest she will be and she will run along from an inside gate. She's raced well in stronger company and went close at her only go at this track. VIIPURI (6) debuts for the Snowden yard and won the first of his two Randwick trials. Looks forward enough and expect a spirited effort with Sherry aboard. TORENDOSETTA (3) has her first run for the Bob Howe stable on a 44-day return. Led and placed at Newcastle first-up and deserves to be kept safe. MATCHSTICKS (8) returns from a lay-off. Coming along well including a recent trial win at Warwick Farm. Worth including.
